        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 4:53PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Olive Branch. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Collierville, Olive Branch, Fairhaven, Miller, Handy Corner, and
Cedarview.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
